Hey @BenGOsborn, I created a simple project with two files:

```solidity
// Foo.sol
pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

contract Foo {
  uint public nonce = 941773313;
}
```

```solidity
// FooDeployer.sol
pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

import "./Foo.sol";

contract FooDeployer {
  address public lastDeploy;

  function deployFoo() public {
    Foo foo = new Foo();

    lastDeploy = address(foo);
  }
}
```

And then I deployed an instance of `Foo` through an instance of `FooDeployer`. I had no problem verifying it.

Do you think you could create a [minimal reproducible example](https://stackoverflow.com/help/minimal-reproducible-example) that shows the problem you are having?
